.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS save
.PP
.I Snapshot current NVRAM state to a JSON file
.PP
.B Category:
Backup
.br
.B Maturity:
stable
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-backup save [FILE] [\-\-force] [\-\-vars\-file OVMF_VARS.fd] [\-\-offline DISK]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B FILE
Output path (default: /var/backups/lamboot\-backup\-<run_id>.json)
.TP
.B \-\-force
Overwrite existing FILE
.TP
.B \-\-vars\-file PATH
Read NVRAM from an OVMF_VARS.fd file (offline mode); requires virt\-fw\-vars
.TP
.B \-\-offline DISK
Also mount DISK to capture LamBoot state files living on the ESP/root (optional; combine with \-\-vars\-file)
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-backup save
sudo lamboot\-backup save /tmp/before\-migration.json
lamboot\-backup save snap.json \-\-vars\-file /var/lib/vz/images/201/vm\-201\-disk\-0.fd
lamboot\-backup save snap.json \-\-vars\-file /path/OVMF_VARS.fd \-\-offline /dev/pve/vm\-201\-disk\-1
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Reads NVRAM via efibootmgr (online) or virt\-fw\-vars (offline via \-\-vars\-file). Never writes NVRAM; read\-only. LamBoot\-specific NVRAM vars (LamBootState, LamBootCrashCount) captured when present. Output is schema\-v1 JSON identical whether source is online or offline.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
Yes \- supports \fB\-\-offline\fR \fIDISK\fR
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Runs unprivileged
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
restore, show, list
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/backup/save
.UE
.RE
.PP
.SS restore
.PP
.I Apply a snapshot (boot order + timeout) to NVRAM
.PP
.B Category:
Backup
.br
.B Maturity:
stable
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-backup restore FILE [\-\-force] [\-\-include\-entries] [\-\-vars\-file OVMF_VARS.fd]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B FILE
Snapshot JSON to restore from
.TP
.B \-\-force
Skip interactive confirmation
.TP
.B \-\-include\-entries
Also attempt to re\-create missing entries (experimental)
.TP
.B \-\-vars\-file PATH
Write NVRAM to an OVMF_VARS.fd file (offline mode); requires virt\-fw\-vars
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-backup restore /tmp/before\-migration.json
sudo lamboot\-backup restore \-\-dry\-run snapshot.json
lamboot\-backup restore snap.json \-\-vars\-file /var/lib/vz/images/201/vm\-201\-disk\-0.fd
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Restores BootOrder + Timeout (+ entries with \-\-include\-entries). Writes NVRAM via efibootmgr (online) or virt\-fw\-vars (offline via \-\-vars\-file). Requires root for online write.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
Yes \- supports \fB\-\-offline\fR \fIDISK\fR
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Requires root (sudo)
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
save, show
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/backup/restore
.UE
.RE
